# Alembic Migrations

This directory contains database migrations managed by Alembic.

## Quick Reference

### Generate a new migration after changing models.py:
```bash
cd backend
alembic revision --autogenerate -m "Description of changes"
```

### Apply all pending migrations:
```bash
alembic upgrade head
```

### Rollback one migration:
```bash
alembic downgrade -1
```

### Check current migration status:
```bash
alembic current
```

### View migration history:
```bash
alembic history
```

## Production Deployment

To run migrations on Supabase production:

1. Set the DATABASE_URL environment variable:
   ```bash
   export DATABASE_URL="postgresql://postgres.xxx:password@aws-0-region.pooler.supabase.com:6543/postgres"
   ```

2. Run migrations:
   ```bash
   alembic upgrade head
   ```
